Shaanxi Green Energy to Expand Its Geothermal Capacity Sixfold

-- B y   O m a r   R .   V a l d i m a r s s o n
-- 
2011-08-30T21:59:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/shaanxi-green-energy-to-expand-its-geothermal-capacity-sixfold.html
The owners of Shaanxi Green Energy
Geothermal Development Company,  China ’s Sinopec Star and
Iceland’s  Enex China , have signed an agreement to expand
Shaanxi’s capacity in geothermal space heating from 3 million
square meters to 20 million square meters.  Once full capacity has been installed, Shaanxi will become
the largest heating utility in the world supplying heat from
geothermal resources, according to an e-mailed statement from
Enex China.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Omar R. Valdimarsson in Reykjavik 
 valdimarsson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
